{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/160°F\/speed 2<b>.","Add milk, flour, eggs and salt and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. The batter should have the consistency of liquid cream. If it seems too thick, add a little milk. Allow batter to rest for at least 30 minutes before using.","Lightly grease a non-stick frying pan (9 in.) with butter and heat on medium-high. Pour in a small ladle of batter, twirling the pan as you pour to cover base of pan completely (crêpe will be approx. 8.5 in. and very thin). Cook for 2-3 minutes or until edges of crêpe are light golden. Turn crêpe over and cook a further 1 minute. Transfer to a plate and cover with a kitchen towel (tea towel) to keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["2 oz unsalted butter, plus extra to fry","21 oz whole milk","9 oz all-purpose flour","4 large eggs","1 pinch salt"]}],"id":"r91177","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-BLe_EGw6sII\/XZae8J8l3aI\/AAAAAAAAgpg\/onBxHEhaq1YhCNPFneR1RhaswgNg5Z4ZwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_dtcrujW0Ui81fbxe.png","title":"Crêpes","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"7 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"21 g","calories":"823 kJ \/ 197 kcal"},"usefulItems":"non-stick pan (9 in.), kitchen towel (tea towel), stove","hintsAndTricks":["To replace butter with oil, omit butter and add <b>2 oz oil<b> along with all other ingredients. Use oil instead of butter for frying.","Flavor the crêpes: add <b>3 tbsp vanilla<b> sugar, <b>1 tsp grated<b> orange zest, or <b>3 oz sugar<b> and <b>2 tbsp rum<b> along with all other ingredients,","Crêpes can be served with sweet or savory fillings.","Crêpes can be frozen for later use. Place a piece of parchment or cling wrap between each crêpe before freezing so they can be easily defrosted. After defrosting, wrap crêpes in foil and warm in a preheated oven (300°F) for 5-10 minutes."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","1h 15m","10 pieces"]}